				\begin{document} $$ y_{i} = \hat{\alpha} + \hat{\theta} z_{i} + \hat{\lambda} x_{i}.  $$ \end{document}yi=α^+θ^zi+λ^xi.

Suppose that this notional study is run and the observed x among those recruited is perfectly uniform on (−0.5,0.5), as depicted by the first horizontal grey bar at the top of Fig. 1. When the misspecified model is fitted, \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
